HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 154
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
A RESOLUTION
To commend Our Lady of Prompt Succor Church and School on the occasion of the
seventy-fifth Our Lady of Prompt Succor Tomato Festival.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Our Lady of Prompt Succor Church and
School for its contributions to the Chalmette community and to commend it on the occasion
of the seventy-fifth Our Lady of Prompt Succor Tomato Festival; and
WHEREAS, the Our Lady of Prompt Succor Parish Tomato Festival began in 1951
and honors the Creole tomato, which is grown exclusively in the mineral-rich, alluvial soil
of St. Bernard and Plaquemines parishes; and
WHEREAS, the family-friendly Tomato Festival is a decades-long tradition that
benefits Our Lady of Prompt Succor Church and School, St. Bernard Parish's only Catholic
school, and helps fund renovations and upgrades; and
WHEREAS, the seventy-fifth Tomato Festival will be held from April 17 through
April 19, 2026, and will feature delicious food, including chargrilled oysters, Tomato-a-la-
Chalmette, barbecue pulled pork, Cuban sandwiches, tacos, crawfish, fried rice, pizza,
hamburgers, and more; the annual Miss, Teen, and Junior Pageant and the Tomato Festival
Children's Pageant each take place on April 18; and
WHEREAS, the Tomato Festival will also feature live entertainment and a collection
of carnival rides and game booths, and its theme is "Rock of Ages"; and
WHEREAS, Our Lady of Prompt Succor Church and School is deserving of
recognition for its continued support of the Tomato Festival and St. Bernard Parish's unique
connection to the Creole tomato.
